# Reinforcement Learning

- Apply this rule only when the project is explicitly RL-focused, the user asks for RL work, or the current files clearly belong to RL training.
- Default to PyTorch unless the repository clearly uses another framework.
- Document non-trivial Tensor shapes at the point of use, for example `# [batch_size, seq_len, hidden_dim]`.
- Consider `wandb` or `MLflow` when experiments need metrics, configs, artifacts, sweeps, or reproducibility notes.
- Keep RL training code modular: separate env, rollout/replay, model, loss, optimizer, eval, and logging.
- For long-running experiments, set seeds explicitly, record hyperparameters and device info, and checkpoint model/optimizer state.
- Log reward, return, episode length, loss terms, learning rate, entropy/KL, and evaluation scores with stable metric names.
- Make device placement explicit; avoid hiding `.to(...)` transfers inside opaque utility functions.
